  <description><![CDATA[<p>In the beautiful Stelvio National Park, you'll find the Hotel Livigno. First founded in 1912 it's the oldest hotel in <a data-udi="umb://document/2924b00d292b448aab37c17b931cf845" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2924b00d292b448aab37c17b931cf845}" title="Livigno">Livigno</a> and has been run by the same family for four generations (the Mottini-Bormolini family). You'll definitely feel the family atmosphere when you stay here. The service is very friendly and personal, so you can relax the minute you walk in the door. The hotel's decorated in a traditional alpine style, with wood-panelled rooms and Persian rugs on the floors.</p>
<p>It's very close to the centre of Livigno, so not only do you have the mountains and national park on your doorstep, but you've got an historical Alpine town to explore. It really is the best of both worlds! What we love about the Hotel Livigno is that it's so close to the Cassana Gondola, which makes it the ideal place if you love hiking, climbing or biking routes. The Gondola will take you up to some of the most stunning view points in Livigno</p>
<p>If all you want to do is relax, then you can do a bit of duty free shopping or take advantage of the hotel's amazing spa. Whether you're hanging out in the Finnish Sauna, paddling in the Turkish bath or steaming in the steam room, the spa's the best way to ease any aches or pains after a busy day.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 2.5 hours by coach from Innsbruck airport.</p>
<p>Throughout September: transfers will go through St. Moritz and take approx. 3.5 hours</p>]]></description>
